# Deferred fixes backlog

This project keeps postponed fixes in **`DEFERRED_FIXES.md`** at the repo root.

## At the start of every session

1. Read `DEFERRED_FIXES.md`.
2. If the **Open** section has items, briefly remind the user (one short bullet list). Do not block work — mention it once, then continue their request.
3. If **Open** is empty, skip the reminder.

## When a deferred item is fixed

1. Remove it from **Open** in `DEFERRED_FIXES.md`.
2. Add a one-line entry under **Done** with the completion date.
3. Do not leave duplicate entries.

## When we discover a new postponed fix

Add it to **Open** in `DEFERRED_FIXES.md` with: symptom, when it happens, cause (if known), fix direction, relevant files, and date added.

Keep entries concise. One concern per item.
